<module>
    <h>dachaidh</h>
    <p><g>dachaidh</g>
        <fem/>
        <en>a home</en></p>

    <section>
        <h>verbs</h>
        <!--<section>
            <h>locative</h>-->
        <module id="thig">
            <h>thig</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=thig">thig</a> ... dhachaidh</g>
                <en>... comes home</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Thàinig mi dhachaidh feasgar.</gd>
                        <tr>I arrived home in the evening.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 21</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha Màiri agus Seumas anns a’ mhonadh an dé. [...] Bha iad glé sgìth
                            nuair a thàinig iad dhachaidh feasgar.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary and James were on the moor yesterday. [...] They were very tired
                            when they came home in the evening.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 76</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An dubhairt iad gu robh iad a’ tighinn dhachaidh an nochd? Thubhairt.</gd>
                        <tr>Did they say that they were coming home tonight? Yes, they did.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 177</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </module>
        <module id="ruith">
            <h>ruith</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=ruith">ruith</a> ... dhachaidh</g>
                <en>... runs home</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Cha do dh’fhan Màiri aig a’ chladach. Ruith i dhachaidh.</gd>
                        <tr>Mary did not stay at the shore. She ran home.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 47</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An do ruith e dhachaidh? Cha do ruith.</gd>
                        <tr>Did he run home? Yes, he did.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 237</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </module>
        <module id="lean">
            <h>lean</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=lean">lean</a> ... dhachaidh</g>
                <en>... follows home</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An do lean an cù dhachaidh thu? Lean.</gd>
                        <tr>Did the dog follow you home? Yes, it did.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 238</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </module>
        <module id="sgriiobh">
            <h>sgrìobh</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=sgriiobh">sgrìobh</a> ... dhachaidh</g>
                <en>... writes home</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An do sgrìobh Calum dhachaidh? Cha do sgrìobh.</gd>
                        <tr>Did Calum write home? No, he didn’t.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 238</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </module>
        <!--</section>-->
    </section>


</module>
